OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEnergy suppliers told to   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Freview soaring direct      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdebits                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, UK energy suppliers have been told to  
OL,6, review the way they charge customers by
OL,7, direct debit amid complaints about     
OL,8, soaring charges and credit balances.   
OL,10,FThe regulator Ofgem also urged six     
OL,11,Fsuppliers to take "immediate" action to
OL,12,Ftackle issues with their charging      
OL,13,Fprocesses.                             
OL,15,FSome 500,000 households saw direct     
OL,16,Fdebit payments double this year, Ofgem 
OL,17,Fsaid, despite prices rising by 54%.    
OL,19,FIt wants suppliers to check whether    
OL,20,Fsuch a large increase was justified.   
